I TOTALLY KNOW THIS WAS MY FAULT but i thought it might not hurt to ask if i can swap these out , the worst they can say is no right ? the manager who came up to the front to answer my question was very much snarky & just kept letting me know how ‘he was losing money’ and ‘this was my fault’ which i totally get , i even said ‘hey if it’s your policy to not let me exchange them, i totally get it, you can say no , i just thought it wouldn’t hurt to ask’ which he then proceeds to tell me i can swap them but the amount of attitude was super unexpected & embarrassing!  he made me feel so bad i only ended up swapping one book, keeping the other damaged books and literally just running out of the store. next time just say no but don’t make someone feel bad when i already felt bad about the books falling in the water in the first place.
